<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-302-654  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 302 654.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  March 26 1990 v11 n13 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hacker puts Internet users on alert; taunts author Cliff Stollabout 'Cuckoo's Egg'. (the Computer Emergency Response Teamwarning to Internet network users)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Swasey, Laurence.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Computer Emergency Response Team (CERT) warns Internet networkusers of potential illegal access of computers on the networkfollowing a message left by a hacker identified only as 'Dave fromAustralia' for Clifford Stoll, author of the book 'The Cuckoo'sEgg' about tracking down a group of West German hackers.andP;  Themessage read, 'Have Cliff read his mail.andP;  The cuckoo has egg onhis face'.andP;  The message was left on the Harvard astronomydepartment computer, which was shut down in an attempt to closeaccess routes into the system used by the hacker.andP;  A telephonecall followed the message two days later during which the hackerboasted of his feat; he used methods outlined in Stoll's book.andO;Stoll says the hacker was angry that Stoll portrayed hackers insuch a poor light in the book.andP;  The hacker claims to have brokeninto Internet sites at Harvard, Boston University, the Universityof Texas at Austin, Purdue University and DEC, according to Stoll.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Access ControlsComputer HackersNetwork ManagementComputer CrimesInternet (Computer network)United States. Computer Emergency Response Team.andO;Person:    Stoll, Cliff (crimes against).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>